Luckily Lunarpine stepped forward so the stone hit him in the back 
instead of the head.He didn't smell any nuts or seeds so he only had 
one conclusion "Maximize", he shouted as he transformed, turned and 
slashed the base of the tree causeing it to tumble forward. as it 
fell he jumped up the side toward Shadow Wings scent. he knew he had 
to move fast so she couldn't fly off.

--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, logomorph@h... wrote:
> ::Shadow Wing::
> 
> She saw him walking around the base of the tree in which she was 
> perched.  She chuckled quietly to herself and pulled the sachel 
under 
> her wing closer to her beak.  She pulled out a nice sized stone 
with 
> her beak and dropped it aiming for Lunarpine's head.  She knew that 
> if she held perfectly still, with his black and white vision, he 
> would be unable to see her high up in the branches.
